Public Enterprises Minister Pravin Gordhan has told the Commission of Inquiry into State Capture that he doesn’t name money through dirty deals and he’s not a commodity for sale. He says the Guptas learnt that while he was Finance minister. Gordhan has been testifying at the commission in Parktown, Johannesburg, where Economic Freedom Fighter (EFF) members and others are demonstrating outside the venue, claiming that Gordhan had a part in state capture. He has challenged all those who claim he enabled state capture to come to the Commission of Inquiry into State Capture and clarify their accusations. Click link for more: 